==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Farad
<hw>Far"ad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Michael
<etsep>Faraday</etsep>, the English electrician.]</ety>
<fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>The standard unit of electrical capacity; the
capacity of a condenser whose charge, having an electro-motive force of
one volt, is equal to the amount of electricity which, with the same
electromotive force, passes through one ohm in one second; the capacity,
which, charged with one coulomb, gives an electro-motive force of one
volt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>faraday</ent>⟦br⟧
